Boil a full #kettle{}.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on high heat.

Fry the @British chicken breast{240%g}(diced) and @sliced mushrooms{180%g}, ~{5-6%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{0.5%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @spinach and ricotta ravioli{250%g}, ~{3%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through.

Next, add the garlic to the mushrooms, fry, ~{1%minute}.

Add the @creme fraiche{150%g}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} and @water{75%ml} (see pantry).

Simmer, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Cook so there's no pink in the middle of the chicken.

Gently stir the ravioli into the sauce.

Share the ravioli between your serving #bowls{}.

Top with the @wild rocket{20%g} leaves and drizzle over the @balsamic glaze{12%ml}.

Enjoy!